      <abstract>
        <p>A novel UV-A-light absorbing N-heterocyclic carbene precursor imidazolium salt <bold>2</bold> was synthesized by reaction of 1,4-bis(pyren-1-yl)-1,4-diazadiene <bold>1</bold> with paraformaldehyde in the presence of chlorotrimethylsilane. The title compound was characterized by <sup>1</sup>H&#x2011;NMR, <sup>13</sup>C&#x2011;NMR, 2D&#x2011;NMR, mass spectrometry, IR and UV/VIS spectroscopy.</p>
      </abstract>
